Control Status of Services

systemctl start ServiceName : Start Service

systemctl stop ServiceName : Stop Service

systemctl status ServiceName : check status of Service

systemctl restart ServiceName : restart service 

systemctl enable ServiceName : service auto start everytime on reboot

systemctl is-enabled ServiceName : check if service is enabled or not

systemctl enable --now ServiceName : enable service and start it immediately

systemctl disable ServiceName : disable service from auto start on reboot

systemctl mask ServiceName : disable service from starting or enabling

systemctl unmask ServiceName : enable service to start or enable

systemctl list-unit-files --type=service : list all services and their status

systemctl list-units --type=service : list all services and their status


